ex:SENS%20motion-webapp-39-release-notes a ex:Action,
        ex:SensorPatchRemovalGuide,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    ex:chunk_id 35 ;
    ex:processRemoval "place one hand against the skin to provide support for the skin while the patch is gently pulled off along the leg. Do not pull away from the skin, but instead pull along the skin. To ease removal, it is recommended to use a skin lotion to help loosen the adhesive. The patch typically begins to loosen itself after 10–14 days"^^xsd:string ;
    ex:recommendedReplacementFrequency 14 ;
    ex:sensorCleaning "After use, patch material is removed from the sensor and the sensor is cleaned for reuse"^^xsd:string ;
    ex:sensorIDLabelHandling "Carefully remove patch material from the sensor, especially around the ID label. If necessary, keep a finger on the label while removing patch material. Should the label fall off, write down the ID and put the sensor with the note aside"^^xsd:string ;
    ex:sensorIDLabelNoteContent "If the label falls off, write down the ID and put the sensor with the note aside"^^xsd:string ;
    ex:sensorIDLabelNoteSource "If the label falls off, write down the ID and put the sensor with the note aside"^^xsd:string ;
    ex:wearingGloves false .

